        <h1>Asigra Backups</h1>
        <p><b><a href="http://tpwiki.eur.ad.tullib.com/download/attachments/14124408/HowTo_Asigra+Linux+Backups.doc?version=1">Asigra Linux Backups Document</a></b></p>

<p><b>Asigra Linux Backups</b>
<br clear="all" /></p>
<ol>
	<li><b>Procedure for Installing the Asigra Backup Client Software</b></li>
</ol>


<p><br clear="all" />
The files for the Asigra backup client can be found in the Linux share:
<br clear="all" />
Ldnr200\ProdSupp:\asigra
<br clear="all" />
Run the setupwin.exe file and then copy the dsuser.jar file to C:\Program Files\DS-User
<br clear="all" />
The backup server (dsclient3) should show up in the top left corner. Tick the box and enter the following details:<br/>
Hostname: Dsclient3<br/>
Username: root<br/>
Password: UK-00t
<br clear="all" /></p>
<ol>
	<li><b>Procedure for checking the nightly backups</b></li>
</ol>


<p><br clear="all" />
On the menu screen click Logs - Activity Log
<br clear="all" />
In the new window (Activity Log viewer) click Find<br/>
This will list all the filesystems which have been backed up the previous night<br/>
As long as the arrow on the left is blue and there are no errors on the Errors column, the backup has been successful.
<br clear="all" /></p>
<ol>
	<li><b>Filesystems being backup up</b></li>
</ol>


<p><br clear="all" /></p>
<ol>
	<li>ldnmbbuild[12] - /etc/apache2 and /var/svn</li>
	<li>ldnmbuatapp[12] - /home/xlsdata/upload</li>
	<li>ldnmbapp[12] - /home/xlsdata/upload</li>
</ol>


<p><br clear="all" /></p>
<ol>
	<li><b>Procedure for adding a backup set</b></li>
</ol>


<p><br clear="all" />
On the server to be backed up:<br/>
Create the account Asigra on the server to be backed up, as follows:<br/>
Username: asigra<br/>
Password: As1gra10<br/>
UID: 1006<br/>
Add to the sudoers file
<br clear="all" />
On dsclient3 asigra server:<br/>
Add the hostname to be backed up to the /etc/hosts file.
<br clear="all" />
On the Asigra software:<br/>
click on Sets - New Backup Set - UNIX_SSH,NFS,Local File System<br/>
Click UNIX-SSH - local host and in the Path change the local host entry with the hostname of the server to be backed up.<br/>
Select 'ask for credentials' and 'sudo as an alternate user'<br/>
Input the Asigra username and password on the next 2 boxes which come up.<br/>
Take the default
<br clear="all" /></p>
